The paper deals with communication and optimization problems, which are typically studied in the Information Theory (cs.IT) and Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) sub-categories. The use of fusion methods and coordinate-wise algorithms suggests a possible fit with the Networked Systems (cs.NI) and Social and Information Networks (cs.SI) sub-categories. Finally, the mention of weighted sum-rate optimization suggests a possible connection with the Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-category.
